iversity, and a substantial introduction by Douglas Brinkley and Patricia Limerick, both of which shed light on DeVoto’s work and legacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aConservation of natural resourcesxWest (U.S.). 0aConservation of natural resourceszWest (U.S.). 0aPublic landszWest (U.S.). 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Sustainable Development.2bisacsh1 aBrinkley, Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrinkley, Douglas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDeVoto, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLimerick, Patricia Nelson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLimerick, Patricia Nelson, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchlesinger, Arthur M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013386840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300133868423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300133868/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles